 • how to narrow a research topic to a specific research question • how to access and organize data that are useful for answering a research question • how to use software such as Stata, SPSS, and SAS to manage data • how to present data so that they convey a clear and effective message   A companion website includes material to enhance the learning experience-specifically statistical software code and the datasets used in the examples, in text format as well as Stata, SPSS, and SAS formats. Visit www.ucpress.edu/go/datamanagement, Downloads tab.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aResearchxData processingxManagement. 0aResearchxMethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520964327423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520964327.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles